hopobject.body: I'm doing an internship street king energy drink uk Bruckner’s last completed symphony was played here by the Vienna Philharmonic, the orchestra that premiered the work’s second version back in 1892. It was a neat idea to preface Bruckner’s great edifice with some organ music. Bruckner was a church organist all his life, and his music is laid out in great unbroken lines and blocks that sit very naturally on an instrument that never has to breathe (not so naturally on an orchestra, perhaps, but we’ll come to that).
